 The accident took place when a bakkie hauling a trailer with another vehicle on it, lost control and overturned. The vehicle was travelling in eMalahleni’s direction and occurred a few kilometres before the Middelburg Toll Plaza.  One of the vehicle’s occupants was taken to hospital by ambulance after sustaining injuries, but fortunately there were no fatalities. Traffic has ground to a halt since motorists are forced to drive on the grass island between lanes. Motorists are urged to proceed with caution.       One dead in early morning crash Fake notes in Belfast leads to two arrests Theft of motor vehicles on the rise Accident claims the life of an infant • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 